body:
@hachikuji @jcustenborder @gwenshap Turns out KAFKA-3260's tests did have an error -- they were trying to assert the exact number of times `SourceTask.commitRecord` be invoked. Just like the producer callbacks in those tests, you can't actually rely on an exact number because the polling is happening in another thread.

This fix adjusts the tests so the producer callbacks and subsequent `SourceTask.commitRecord` calls are handled in the same way. Ideally we'd also be able to check that they were invoked the same number of times. The errors seem to currently be masked because exceptions about incorrect mock method calls were getting eaten up by the WorkerSourceTask thread, and not reported to the main test thread.

Longer term, it probably makes more sense to try to test each of the threads independently so we don't run into these issues, but this should correct the immediate issue for tests.
